## Best Practices

### 1. Goal Lifecycle Hygiene

**Weekly:**
- Run `check_review_needed()` to catch stale goals
- Update progress on all In Progress goals
- Generate health report

**Bi-Weekly:**
- Review potential goals and prioritize top choices
- Archive completed goals with retrospectives

**Monthly:**
- Generate comprehensive monthly report
- Review velocity and adjust estimates
- Update roadmap diagram for stakeholders

**Quarterly:**
- Deep retrospective analysis
- Tier rebalancing
- Strategic planning with brainstorming session

### 2. Health Score Targets

| Grade | Score | Target Audience | Action Needed |
|-------|-------|----------------|---------------|
| A | 90-100 | Mature teams | Maintain practices |
| B | 80-89 | Growing teams | Minor adjustments |
| C | 70-79 | New teams | Review processes |
| D | 60-69 | Struggling teams | Intervention required |
| F | <60 | Crisis mode | Major restructuring |

### 3. Tier Management

**Now Tier:**
- Maximum 3-5 goals
- Review daily/weekly
- High urgency items only

**Next Tier:**
- Maximum 5-8 goals
- Review weekly
- Ready to start when Now capacity opens

**Later Tier:**
- Maximum 10-15 goals
- Review monthly
- Planned but not immediate

**Someday Tier:**
- No limit
- Review quarterly
- Ideas worth keeping but not scheduled

### 4. Retrospective Quality

**Good Retrospective:**
```yaml
retrospective:
  whatWorked:
    - "Daily standups kept team aligned"
    - "Early user testing caught UX issues"

  whatDidntWork:
    - "Assumed database migration would be trivial"
    - "Underestimated design iteration time"

  lessonsLearned:
    - "Always test migrations in staging first"
    - "Budget 50% more time for UI polish"
    - "Involve QA from day 1, not at the end"

  estimateAccuracy: off_by_more
  actualEffort: Very High
  wouldDoAgain: yes_with_changes
```

**Poor Retrospective:**
```yaml
retrospective:
  whatWorked: ["Everything went well"]
  whatDidntWork: ["Nothing major"]
  lessonsLearned: ["N/A"]
  estimateAccuracy: accurate
```

